# UI Components and Theming Guidelines

## Theme Usage
The app uses a comprehensive theming system defined in [lib/core/themes/app_theme.dart](mdc:lib/core/themes/app_theme.dart).

### Color Usage
- Use `AppColors` constants for all colors
- Never hardcode color values
- Follow the established color scheme:
  - `AppColors.primaryColor` for primary actions
  - `AppColors.backgroundColor` for backgrounds
  - `AppColors.primaryTextColor` for main text
  - `AppColors.containerFillColor` for containers

### Typography
- Use predefined text styles from the theme
- Follow Material 3 typography scale
- Use `OpenSans` font family consistently
- Text styles available:
  - `Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineLarge` for main headings
  - `Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleMedium` for section headers
  - `Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium` for body text
  - `Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelMedium` for labels

## Responsive Design
Use `flutter_screenutil` for responsive sizing:

```dart
// Screen dimensions
ScreenUtil().screenWidth
ScreenUtil().screenHeight

// Responsive sizing
Container(
  width: 100.w,    // 100 screen width units
  height: 50.h,    // 50 screen height units
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(16.r), // 16 responsive units
  child: Text(
    'Hello',
    style: TextStyle(fontSize: 16.sp), // 16 responsive font size
  ),
)
```

## Component Guidelines

### Buttons
- Use `ElevatedButton` for primary actions
- Use `OutlinedButton` for secondary actions
- Use `TextButton` for text-only actions
- All buttons use theme-defined styles

### Input Fields
- Use `TextFormField` with theme decoration
- Include proper validation
- Use appropriate keyboard types
- Show clear error messages

### Cards and Containers
- Use `Card` widget with theme styling
- Apply consistent border radius (12px)
- Use proper elevation and shadows
- Fill with `AppColors.containerFillColor`

### AppBar
- Use transparent background
- Include proper title styling
- Use theme-defined icon colors
- Handle system overlay styles

## Custom Widgets
Create reusable widgets in the `lib/widgets/` directory:

```dart
class CustomWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const CustomWidget({
    super.key,
    required this.title,
    this.onTap,
  });
  
  final String title;
  final VoidCallback? onTap;
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container(
      // Implementation
    );
  }
}
```

## Screen Structure
Follow this pattern for screens:

```dart
class FeatureView extends StatelessWidget {
  const FeatureView({super.key});
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return GetBuilder<FeatureController>(
      builder: (controller) => Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(title: Text('Title')),
        body: _buildBody(context, controller),
      ),
    );
  }
  
  Widget _buildBody(BuildContext context, FeatureController controller) {
    // Screen content
  }
}
```

## Accessibility
- Use semantic labels
- Provide proper contrast ratios
- Support screen readers
- Include proper focus management